And the great judgment of YHWH shall come upon all flesh. The giants and the Watchers shall be cast into the eternal fire and their spirits shall be bound in the valleys of darkness until the end of all ages. The righteous shall inherit the earth and peace shall reign forever under the throne of the Most High.
Then Enoch the scribe was taken up and shown the tablets of heaven. He wrote down the judgment and sent it to the giants and their fathers the Watchers. And the giants trembled and Mahaway the son of Baraqiel flew to Enoch seeking interpretation of the dreams.
And in the dream a garden was uprooted and its trees burned. Only three roots remained. And another dream came of a tablet being thrown into the water and only two lines survived. These things foretold the destruction of the giants and the flood that would cleanse the earth.
The giants devoured the flesh of men and drank their blood. They committed violence upon the earth and all creation groaned under their oppression. The cries of the slain reached heaven and the four holy archangels brought the complaint before the throne of YHWH.
Ohya and Hahya the sons of the Watchers saw terrifying dreams. They saw a stone tablet sinking into the waters and only three names remained. They saw trees being uprooted and fire consuming all but three roots. They feared the judgment that was coming upon them and upon their fathers the Watchers who had descended upon Mount Hermon.
The Watchers who came down in the days of Jared took wives from the daughters of men and taught them every kind of wickedness — sorcery, enchantments, the forging of weapons, and the making of cosmetics. And they begat great giants who consumed all the produce of the earth and then turned to devour mankind itself.

